cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SFL Meaning Matrix LLM"
message: >-
  If you use this architecture, the semiotic manifold specification,
  or any component of this repository in research, please cite as below.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Drury
    given-names: Simon
repository-code: https://github.com/simon-drury/sfl-meaning-matrix-llm
license: CC-BY-NC-4.0
date-released: "2026-04-10"
version: "0.1.0"
abstract: >
  A research architecture grounding transformer-based language models in
  Systemic Functional Linguistics (SFL). The transformer operates on a
  six-dimensional semiotic manifold encoding the SFL metafunctions
  (ideational, field, interpersonal, tenor, textual, mode). Input and
  output modality are handled at the edges; the transformer is
  modality-blind. English and Spanish are co-equal first languages;
  there is no translation step. The architecture supports persistent
  context via a reference meaning state M_0 carried as structured
  metadata across processes.
keywords:
  - systemic functional linguistics
  - semiotic manifold
  - large language models
  - multimodal
  - multilingual
  - meaning-first architecture
  - transformer
  - SFL
